Method Detail

printHeader

protected void printHeader()
Prints the information that this class needs to go to the header. This method should be overriden if you intend to put anything in the header file. When you override the method, you're going to want to make the following call to get you setup and going: CodeBlock block = this.hBlock("first line of block"); Notice that you do not need to (nor should you) include the "{".

printImplementation

protected void printImplementation()
Prints the information that this class needs to go to the implementation file. This method should be overriden if you intend to put anything in the implementation file. When you override the method, you're going to want to make the following call to get you setup and going: CodeBlock block = this.cppBlock("first line of block"); Notice that you do not need to (nor should you) include the "{".

addField

public void addField(JavaField field)
JavaField registers itself with its scope's field list because of the multiple declaration problem. All classes containing a field list must implement this.

hasField

Check if we have this field. Objects that have populated field lists must implement this.

getField

public JavaField getField(java.lang.String field)
Get the field from the field list. If we don't have the field, ask our parent scope. This should never run all the way to the top because we're only translating working java.

hBlock

protected final CodeBlock hBlock(java.lang.String header)
Sets up a cpp block for printing to the header. This function is provided here, rather than in a constructor, because you need to know the header information before you begin to print. That is, you need to know what goes on the line before the "{" before you can start a code block, so this just helps with that. This also does some work in the background to make print seamless for you.

cppBlock

protected final CodeBlock cppBlock(java.lang.String header)

That is, you need to know what goes on the line before the "{" before you can start a code block, so this just helps with that. This also does some work in the background to make print seamless for you.
